Sentencing proceedings against convicted double-murderer, Vincenzo Pietropaolo, have been postponed in the Johannesburg High Court. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Sentencing proceedings against convicted double-murderer Vincenzo Pietropaolo have been postponed in the Johannesburg High Court. The court has granted Pietropaolo his application to get a social worker for his pre-sentencing statement. READ: Judgment handed down in Pietropaolo murder case On Tuesday, the court found him guilty of killing his father in March 2017 and his wife in November of the same year. Pietropaolo is the former treasurer of the Bank of Athens.